@Node Usage "RevFlex V1.0: Usage"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
 @{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} U S A G E @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} @{B}|@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯@{UB}@{FG Text}
  Just like FlexRev RevFlex has following argument template plus the INCBUILD option:

@{B}REVFILE/A,TARGET,PROTO,IR=INCREVISION/S,IV=INCVERSION/S,IB=INCBUILD/S@{UB}

@{B}REVFILE/A@{UB}        - The filename of the REVISION file.
@{B}TARGET@{UB}           - The name of the target file to be produced.  This is
                   optional and can be omitted as long as TARGET is defined in
                   the revision file.
@{B}PROTO@{UB}            - The name of the prototype file.  This is optional and can be
                   omitted as long as PROTO is defined in the revision file.
@{B}IR=INCREVISION/S@{UB} - Bump the the revision number.
@{B}IV=INCVERSION/S@{UB}  - Bumb the version number.
@{B}IB=INCBUILD/S@{UB}    - Bump the build number.
@{B}VERBOSE=DEBUG/S@{UB}  - This will generate a more detailed output from RevFlex.
                   DEBUG is a bit misleading and is only here because FelxRev
                   had an option called DEBUG.



